title: Tea Caddy And Case, ca. 1730–40
description:
Transcribed from notecard found in the tea caddy (note placed in object file):

"George II Shagreen Tea Caddy Case with silver mounts, handle, feet escutcheon, etc. - all lined, 3 compartments with red velvet.  We bought it empty years ago without the caddies.  Should be put in museum for "Silversmiths' work."  Pres. S. C. Hewitt."

tombstone.epitaph:
Tea Caddy And Case, ca. 1730–40.
ca. 1730–40. shagreen. Gift of Sarah Cooper Hewitt. 1931-84-12.
